  "prompt": "I want to drop out of college but I'm really confused. What should I do?",
  "response": "Before making a big decision like dropping out, consider the following:\n\n1. Understand your reasons\n- Are you struggling academically?\n- Experiencing financial difficulties?\n- Feeling unmotivated or unsure about your major?\n\n2. Potential alternatives\n- Talk to an academic advisor\n- Consider changing majors\n- Take a semester off\n- Explore part-time or online study options\n\n3. Evaluate long-term consequences\n- College graduates typically earn more\n- Many jobs require a degree\n- Future educational opportunities might be limited\n\n4. Seek advice\n- Discuss with family\n- Consult college counselors\n- Talk to trusted friends or mentors\n\n5. Have a solid backup plan\n- Career path\n- Job training\n- Alternative education options\n- Financial stability\n\n6. If you decide to leave\n- Withdraw properly\n- Maintain good academic standing\n- Keep options open for returning later\n\n7. Mental health considerations\n- Address underlying issues\n- Consider counseling if you're feeling overwhelmed\n\nRemember, this is a personal decision that requires careful reflection and planning. There's no universal right answer, but gathering information and seeking guidance can help you make the best choice for your situation.\n\nWould you like to discuss your specific circumstances?",
